# Local-First Cursor Rule

- Follow `.cursor/rules/local-first-model-routing.mdc` as the canonical AI routing standard.
- Prefer local models for simple coding, edits, debugging, explanations, and drafting.
- Escalate only when local inference fails twice, context limits block completion, freshness/web access is required, or the task is high-risk.
- Keep prompts scoped to the smallest relevant files and avoid visible routing/delegation footers.
